Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Chop into 2cm sized chunks. Chop the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} into
thirds.

Pour the boiling @water{240%ml} for the bulgur wheat into a #saucepan{} and
bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g},
bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the pan
and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until
ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Once
hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g}, pepper and @chermoula spice mix{1}
(add less if you don't like heat). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir to
combine.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Fry until the chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{9-11%minutes}, stir
occasionally. Lower the heat if the chicken and pepper start to go too dark.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the Tenderstem® to the chicken. Add a splash of water, cover with a lid.
Cook for ~{4-6%minutes}, until the Tenderstem® is tender, but still crunchy.

When cooked, fluff up the bulgur with a #fork{}. Stir through the
@harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you don't like heat). Add the bulgur to the
chicken and veg and gently mix together until combined. Taste and add salt and
pepper if needed.

Spoon the bulgur, chicken and veg into #bowls{}. Drizzle some
@low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} over the top. Enjoy!

> Step 3 Modularity: If you've opted to get diced chicken breast instead of
> diced chicken thigh, cook the recipe in the same way it tells you to cook the
> chicken thigh.